The opposition Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) in Cross River State has described Governor Benedict Ayade’s recent declaration to contest for president.
Chairman of the party in the state, Venatius Ikem made the reaction in an interaction with pressmen in Calabar Friday.
Ikem said the governor was desperate because he has failed in the state.
He said everybody in Nigeria and beyond know Ayade as a professional joker and would not be taken seriously.
